# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version ^1.6.1 to dependencies
- Used npm (the project's package manager) to install the package

### 2. Modified Files

**crypto-signal-dashboard/app/layout.tsx**
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag after `<SpeedInsights />` and `{children}`
- Followed the existing pattern used for Speed Insights to maintain consistency

**crypto-signal-dashboard/package.json**
- Added `"@vercel/analytics": "^1.6.1"` to the dependencies section

**crypto-signal-dashboard/package-lock.json**
- Updated with the new package and its dependencies (1643 packages total)

## Implementation Details

This project uses:
- **Next.js App Router** (app directory structure)
- **npm** as the package manager
- **TypeScript** for type safety

The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.tsx`) following Next.js App Router best practices. It's placed after the children and SpeedInsights components inside the body tag, which ensures it loads on all pages without interfering with the main content.

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter passed with no new errors (`npm run lint`)
✅ Package.json and package-lock.json properly updated
✅ TypeScript types correctly resolved

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics documentation for App Router projects and maintains consistency with the existing code structure.
